## Model Metadata

### Required Fields Per Version

| Field | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| training_data_version | Data version or hash |
| training_date | When the model was trained |
| framework_versions | Python, sklearn, torch, etc. |
| feature_schema | Input feature names, types, ranges |
| performance_metrics | Key offline metrics |
| author | Who trained/registered the model |
| approval | Who approved for production |

---

## Anti-Patterns

| Anti-Pattern | Why It's Bad | Correct Approach |
|--------------|--------------|------------------|
| Overwriting production model in place | No rollback possible | Version and alias |
| No metadata on model versions | Can't reproduce or audit | Required metadata fields |
| Skipping staging | Untested in prod conditions | Always stage first |
| Manual file-based deployment | Error-prone, no audit trail | Use model registry |
